23bf66b1-471a-401f-b47a-4d6078b5af7f.03b7dfef-2e8c-480e-abb8-d7c1f14f0af2.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
    string1 - The first string. 
Default value\: "" (empty)
    string2 - The second string.
Default value\: "" (empty)
    ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

Responses\:
    true - If the two strings are equal.
    false - If the two strings are not equal.

23bf66b1-471a-401f-b47a-4d6078b5af7f.29ec5f92-d1f1-46c5-9b24-bb48c032bc22.description=Waits for the job to reach a specific state. If no state is specified, then this will wait for the job to reach an end state. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobID - The id of the job. status - The status to wait for the job to reach. If none is specified this will wait until the job is no longer running. timeout - The maximum number of milliseconds to wait for the job. If not specified, 1 hour is used. frequency - The frequency, in milliseconds, with which the operation will check if the job has reached the specified state (or an end state). The default value is 5000 ms. Responses\: failure - Something went wrong. success - The operation completed successfully. 23bf66b1-471a-401f-b47a-4d6078b5af7f.442a38ee-c7ea-47dc-9312-069c009dc208.description=Run communication test on the given SA server or device group. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to Connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. attachableName - The names of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. attachableID - The ids of either the servers, or the device groups, separated by 'separator'. If provided, the 'attachableName' will be ignored. attachableType - The type of the attachable items. Can be one of the following values\: SERVER or DEVICE_GROUP. timeout - Timeout in milliseconds, to wait for the job to finish. Default value is 0. separator - The separator used for separating the inputs. The default value for the separator is comma (,). Responses\: success - retrieved successfully failure - failed to retrieve data Returns\: returnResult - The id of the job created. 23bf66b1-471a-401f-b47a-4d6078b5af7f.89223a39-3f4f-4ff0-8509-0bcfcd66a6bd.description=

23bf66b1-471a-401f-b47a-4d6078b5af7f.ee39654c-0b96-4eb7-9665-3a083f8a6556.description=Retrieves the output of a run communication test job. Inputs\: coreHost - The DNS name or IP Address of your SAS core. corePort - The port to connect to your SAS core on. coreProtocol - The protocol to connect to your SAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS. coreUsername - The username for host. corePassword - The password for host. coreVersion - The version of SAS to use. jobId - The ID of the Run Communication Test job. separator - The separator used for separating the results. The default value for the separator is a comma (,). Outputs\: serverName - The names of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. serverID - The IDs of the servers against which the run communication test job was ran. agentReachable - The flags indicating, for each server, if the SA agent is reachable. securityOK - The flags indicating if the encryption and security between each server and the SA core are OK. commandEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve commands to be executed from the SA core. dataAccessEngine - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve its stored device information from the SA core. softwareRepository - The flags indicating, for each server, if it can retrieve software and patches from the SA core. machineID - The flags indicating, for each server, if its machine ID matches the one stored in the SA core. reachabilityTime - The reachability time, for each server. lifecycle - The lifecycle of each server. osVersion - The OS version of each server. Responses\: success - The operation has completed successfully. failure - The operation has failed.
